    "short description": "New Russian MFSK Modem that uses 68 MFSK (5 tones at a time) as well as a 9000 Bd 8-PSK insert every second which spans 10 kHz wide. This signal is often found attributed with CIS-3000, where CIS-3000 acts as the ALE for this signal as well as CIS-128. It is used by Russian diplomatic services and known with the unofficial name \"Perelivt\".",
